        "event": "Flood Advisory",
        "sender": "w-nws.webmaster@noaa.gov",
        "senderName": "NWS Omaha/Valley NE",
        "headline": "Flood Advisory issued June 7 at 8:04PM CDT until June 7 at 11:00PM CDT by NWS Omaha/Valley NE",
        "description": "* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.\n\n* WHERE...Northwestern Cuming County in northeastern Nebraska...\nSoutheastern Wayne County in northeastern Nebraska...\n\n* WHEN...Until 1100 PM CDT.\n\n* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...\n- At 758 PM CDT, local law enforcement reported heavy rain is\nleading to flooding in portions of northwestern Cuming County,\nincluding near the intersections of 4.5 Road and W, and 6th and\nX. Minor flooding is already occurring. Between 3 and 4 inches of\nrain have fallen.\n- This includes the following streams and drainages...\nPlum Creek, Rattlesnake Creek, Kane Creek, Logan Creek Dredge,\nSand Creek, Dry Creek, Coon Creek and Elkhorn River. Flooding\nimpacts will continue, but no additional rainfall is expected.\n- Some locations that will experience flooding include...\nMainly rural areas of Northwestern Cuming and Southeastern Wayne\nCounties.\n- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood",
        "instruction": "Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood\ndeaths occur in vehicles.\n\nBe aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.",
        "response": "Avoid",
        "note": null,
