        "sender": "w-nws.webmaster@noaa.gov",
        "senderName": "NWS Hastings NE",
        "headline": "Flood Warning issued June 7 at 1:56PM CDT until June 8 at 10:00AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE",
        "description": "* WHAT...Small stream flooding caused by Friday night's excessive\nrainfall continues.\n\n* WHERE...York County in east central Nebraska...\nNorthern Fillmore County in south central Nebraska...\nSoutheastern Hamilton County in south central Nebraska...\n\n* WHEN...Until 1000 AM CDT Monday.\n\n* IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying\nand flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring. Expect many\nareas of slow moving or standing water.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...\n- At 150 PM CDT, emergency management reported continued flooding\nin the warned area. Flooding is already occurring. Between 2 and\n5 inches of rain Friday night continues to result in runoff\nthrough area creeks and rivers.\n- This includes the following streams and drainages...\nWest Fork Big Blue River, Lincoln Creek, and Beaver Creek\nFlooding impacts will continue, but no additional rainfall is\nexpected. River gauges indicate continued flooding along the West\nFork Big Blue River from Grafton to McCool Junction.\n- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood",
        "instruction": "Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.",
        "response": "Avoid",
        "note": null,
        "parameters": {
          "AWIPSidentifier": [
            "FLWGID"
          ],
          "WMOidentifier": [
            "WGUS43 KGID 071856"
